<br>
With the old UI, I brought my spell gems into hotboxes.  I liked the 2 column 4 row layout better.  So, normally, it looks like this:<br>
<br>
main nuke | assist button<br>
snare     | root<br>
AE / AoE  | Lure<br>
<br>
For my enchanter, its like this:<br>
mez       | assist button<br>
tash      | AE mez<br>
AoE Stun  | Mem blur<br>
<br>
My wizard has a few right click items, JBoots, staff of temp flux and horse.  (No epic yet, sigh)  So, I am tring to find a way to drop those in there as well.  The enchanter doesn't have any yet ... not even sure what I can get.  (OT: Does anyone know a site like graffe.com that is geared towards enchanters ? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One thing I have found that I really like for the buff windows, is a list of buffs.  I can't remeber the URL.  But, on eqinterface.com there is a buff window (thats apart of another package) that will display the buff icon next to the word explaining what the buff is.  It will show buffs in a blue box and debuffs in a red box.  That mod really rocks, I can see in a split sec that I have a DoT on me, or something else.<br>
<br>
The animation on yours I think you should remove, personally.  It takes CPU cycles to proccess it, and its really quite usless.<br>
<br>
The outline you created around all your boxes is much nicer then some I have seen.  But, it still kinda takes up too much space.  I am tring everything I can to make things as small as possiable, without making it impossiable to work with.<br>
<br>
I saw a screen shot recently of a raid.  I don't know the URL.  But, instead of putting the chars current HPs / max HPs in a seperate space.  They actually placed it right on top of the bar.  Its hard to discribe.  Maybe someone here knows what I am talking about.  I would really like to do something like that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Heres an idea.  How about putting a cast bar right above your main nukes.  Not fully sure how you would wedge it in there, but I think it would be a very nice addition.<br>
<br>
